Apple has a long list of devices that it plans to launch during the first half of 2026, <em><a href="https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-07-10/apple-plans-new-macbook-pro-iphone-17e-and-ipads-by-early-2026">Bloomberg</a></em>'s <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/guide/mark-gurman/">Mark Gurman</a> said today. Apple is working on an <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/guide/iphone/">iPhone</a> 17e, along with several Macs and iPads.<br/>
<br/>
<img src="https://images.macrumors.com/article-new/2025/06/apple-beta-26-lineup.jpg" alt="" width="2000" height="1125" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1005210" /><br/>
Here's what's in the works for 2026:<br/>
<ul><br/>
 	<li><strong>iPhone 17e</strong> - Updated A19 chip, could launch in February.</li><br/>
 	<li><strong>MacBook Air</strong> - M5 chips.</li><br/>
 	<li><strong>MacBook Pro</strong> - M5 chips.</li><br/>
 	<li><strong>Updated Apple Display</strong> - A follow up to the <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/studio-display/">Apple Studio Display</a> and Pro Display XDR.</li><br/>
 	<li><strong>Low-cost iPad</strong> - Will get a faster chip. Slated for March/April.</li><br/>
 	<li><strong>iPad Air</strong> - Expected to get M4 chip. March/April launch timeline.</li><br/>
 	<li><strong>Smart home hub</strong> - Expected in the first half of next year.</li><br/>
</ul><br/>
Later this year, Apple plans to launch new <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/iphone-17/">iPhone 17</a> models, new versions of the Apple Watch, Apple Watch Ultra, and <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/apple-watch-se/">Apple Watch SE</a>, and new <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/roundup/ipad-pro/">iPad Pro</a> models.<div class="linkback">Tags: <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/guide/bloomberg-com/">Bloomberg</a>, <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/guide/mark-gurman/">Mark Gurman</a></div><br/>This article, &quot;<a href="https://www.macrumors.com/2025/07/10/these-apple-products-are-coming-in-early-2026/">These Apple Products Are Coming in Early 2026</a>&quot; first appeared on <a href="https://www.macrumors.com">MacRumors.com</a><br/><br/><a href="https://forums.macrumors.com/threads/these-apple-products-are-coming-in-early-2026.2461337/">Discuss this article</a> in our forums<br/><br/>